---
import DocsNav from '../../components/DocsNav.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import SiteNav from '../../components/SiteNav.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Configuration · neondeck"
  description="Runtime home, config files, secrets, models, providers, repositories, schedules, SOUL, and skills in neondeck."
>
  <div class="site-shell">
    <SiteNav />
    <main class="container docs-layout">
      <DocsNav />
      <article class="docs-prose">
        <h1>Configuration</h1>
        <p>
          neondeck keeps mutable local state outside the repository. The app
          resolves runtime home from <code>NEONDECK_HOME</code>, then
          <code>XDG_CONFIG_HOME/neondeck</code>, then
          <code>~/.config/neondeck</code>.
        </p>

        <h2>Runtime home</h2>
        <pre><code>~/.config/neondeck/
  .env
  config.json
  repos.json
  dashboard.json
  dashboard.schema.json
  schedules.json
  SOUL.md
  skills/
    custom-skill/
      SKILL.md
  data/
    neondeck.db
    flue.db</code></pre>
        <p>
          <code>data/neondeck.db</code> stores app state: watches, scheduler jobs,
          notifications, memories, workflow summaries, config history, and execution
          approvals. <code>data/flue.db</code> stores Flue runtime state.
        </p>

        <h2>Secrets</h2>
        <p>
          Packaged and local app secrets live in runtime-home <code>.env</code>.
          Repo-root <code>.env</code> is supported as a checkout-only fallback when
          runtime-home <code>.env</code> does not define a value. Process environment
          variables still take precedence.
        </p>
        <pre><code>KILOCODE_API_KEY=...
KILOCODE_ORGANIZATION_ID=...
FLUE_AGENT_MODEL=kilocode/kilo/auto
GITHUB_TOKEN=...
GITHUB_LOGIN=...</code></pre>

        <h2>Models and providers</h2>
        <p>
          Agent model choices live in <code>config.json</code>. Model strings
          must be provider-qualified and use providers already registered by the
          app or Flue runtime.
        </p>
        <pre><code>&#123;
  "version": 1,
  "models": &#123;
    "displayAssistant": "kilocode/kilo/auto",
    "subagents": &#123;
      "default": "kilocode/kilo/auto",
      "repoResearcher": "kilocode/kilo/auto",
      "ciInvestigator": "kilocode/kilo/auto",
      "releaseReviewer": "kilocode/kilo/auto"
    &#125;
  &#125;,
  "providers": &#123;
    "kilocode": &#123;
      "enabled": true,
      "apiKeyEnv": "KILOCODE_API_KEY",
      "organizationIdEnv": "KILOCODE_ORGANIZATION_ID"
    &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>
        <p>
          Provider config stores environment variable names, not raw secrets or
          arbitrary endpoints. Provider registration changes require a server
          restart.
        </p>

        <h2>Repositories</h2>
        <p>
          <code>repos.json</code> maps repo ids to local git checkouts and GitHub
          repository metadata. A local checkout is required for local git status and
          repo diagnostics. GitHub API features use <code>GITHUB_TOKEN</code>
          and do not expose the token to the browser.
        </p>

        <h2>Dashboard</h2>
        <p>
          <code>dashboard.json</code> selects theme, layout regions, plugin ids, and
          plugin config. The checked-in dashboard config and schema are copied into
          new runtime homes as defaults.
        </p>

        <h2>Schedules and watches</h2>
        <p>
          <code>schedules.json</code> contains schedule blueprints. Active scheduler
          jobs and PR/release watches are persisted in SQLite so they survive restart.
        </p>

        <h2>SOUL and skills</h2>
        <p>
          <code>SOUL.md</code> defines the agent name, emoji, and vibe. User runtime
          skills live under <code>skills/</code>, plus any external skill roots
          listed in <code>config.json</code>. Start a new session or restart the
          server after changing SOUL, model choices, memory, or skills so prompt
          context reloads deliberately.
        </p>
      </article>
    </main>
    <SiteFooter />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
